      "content": "Increased border security and strict enforcement are essential to uphold the rule of law and prevent the exploitation of illegal crossings by criminal gangs and human traffickers. These measures also protect national sovereignty by ensuring that only qualified individuals enter the country, which is crucial for maintaining a fair and orderly economy. Furthermore, prioritizing enforcement allows the government to focus resources on integrating lawfully admitted immigrants and addressing the root causes of migration through robust domestic solutions.",
